## 2. YAML Configuration File Structure

### 2.1 Standard Structure

```yaml
# app_config - Application configuration
app_config:
  main_window_name: "Window Title"        # Main window title (required)
  head_keys: ["Column1", "Column2"]       # Table header keywords (required for table pages)

# elements - Element locator configuration
elements:
  # Button element
  button_name:
    automation_id: "btnId"           # AutomationId (preferred)
    name: "Button Text"              # Name property (alternative)
    type: "Button"                   # Control type (optional, used for combined locating)
  
  # Input element
  input_name:
    automation_id: "txtInput"
    type: "Edit"
  
  # Window element (nested child elements)
  dialog_window:
    automation_id: "DialogId"
    name: "Dialog Title"
    type: "Window"
    child_elements:                  # Child elements definition
      confirm_button:
        automation_id: "btnConfirm"
      cancel_button:
        automation_id: "btnCancel"
  
  # Table element
  content_table:
    name: "DataGridView"             # Tables usually use name locator
    # automation_id: "dataGrid"      # Or use automation_id

# test_data - Test data (AI auto-generated template)
test_data:
  # Test scenario name
  scenario_name:
    param1: "value1"
    param2: "value2"
```

### 2.2 Common Dialogs Configuration

**IMPORTANT**: Common dialogs are defined in `common_dialogs.yaml`, pages **DO NOT need to redefine them**.

ConfigManager automatically loads and merges the following common dialogs:
- `operation_window` - Operation prompt window (Yes/No/Exit buttons)
- `prompt_window` - Message prompt window (Confirm button only)
- `delete_confirm_window` - Delete confirmation window
- `reset_password_window` - Reset password window
- `error_message_window` - Error message window

**Override Rule**: Pages can redefine same-named dialogs if special locators are needed.

